Note:
This file handles points-to analysis for pointer aliasing.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process points-to set computation for all pointers
- Handle flow-sensitive and context-sensitive analysis
- Manage points-to graph construction and propagation
- Process alias query resolution for optimizations

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Points-to analysis enables precise alias analysis
- Proper points-to information improves optimization safety
- Points-to analysis is foundation for advanced optimizations

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Points-to set computation using Andersen's inclusion-based analysis
- Constraint graph construction and propagation
- Flow-insensitive whole-program analysis
- Alias query interface for optimization passes

Dependencies:
- compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/mir.runa (MIR structures, instructions)
- compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa (Type information)
- compiler/middle/analysis/control_flow.runa (CFG structures)
- compiler/middle/analysis/data_flow.runa (def-use chains)
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa (OWNED HEAP allocation - Tier 3)
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa (constraint lists)
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa (pointer mappings)
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/set.runa (points-to sets)
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa (debug printing)
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/mir.runa" as MIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/middle/analysis/control_flow.runa" as CFG
Import "compiler/middle/analysis/data_flow.runa" as DataFlow
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dictionary
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/set.runa" as Set
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTRAINT TYPE CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Andersen's constraint types
Constant CONSTRAINT_ADDR_OF as Integer is 1      Note: p = &q (address-of)
Constant CONSTRAINT_COPY as Integer is 2         Note: p = q (copy)
Constant CONSTRAINT_LOAD as Integer is 3         Note: p = *q (load/dereference)
Constant CONSTRAINT_STORE as Integer is 4        Note: *p = q (store/assignment through pointer)

Note: ============================================================================
Note: POINTS-TO ANALYSIS TYPE DEFINITIONS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
AbstractLocation represents an abstract memory location in points-to analysis.

Each allocation site in the program creates an abstract location. Pointers
point to abstract locations, not concrete addresses.

Fields:
- location_id: Unique identifier for this location
- allocation_site: Instruction where this location is allocated
- type_info: HIR type information for this allocation
- is_heap: Boolean: 1 if heap allocated, 0 if stack
- is_global: Boolean: 1 if global variable, 0 if local
- is_parameter: Boolean: 1 if function parameter
- name: Optional name string (for debugging)

Memory: Tier 3 (OWNED HEAP)
Size: 7 fields × 8 bytes = 56 bytes
@End Reasoning

Type called "AbstractLocation":
    location_id as Integer      Note: Unique location ID
    allocation_site as Integer  Note: Pointer to allocating instruction
    type_info as Integer        Note: Pointer to HIRTypeInfo
    is_heap as Integer          Note: Boolean: heap allocation
    is_global as Integer        Note: Boolean: global variable
    is_parameter as Integer     Note: Boolean: function parameter
    name as Integer             Note: Pointer to name string (optional)
End Type

Note: Field offsets: 0, 8, 16, 24, 32, 40, 48

@Reasoning
PointsToSet represents the set of abstract locations a pointer may point to.

For a pointer p, pts(p) is the set of all abstract locations that p may
point to at any program point. This is flow-insensitive (whole program view).

Fields:
- pointer_id: The pointer variable ID
- pointees: Set of AbstractLocation IDs this pointer may point to
- is_unknown: Boolean: if true, may point to anything (conservative)
- is_null: Boolean: may be null pointer

Memory: Tier 3 (OWNED HEAP)
Size: 4 fields × 8 bytes = 32 bytes
@End Reasoning

Type called "PointsToSet":
    pointer_id as Integer       Note: Pointer variable ID
    pointees as Integer         Note: Set of location IDs
    is_unknown as Integer       Note: Boolean: conservative unknown
    is_null as Integer          Note: Boolean: may be null
End Type

Note: Field offsets: 0, 8, 16, 24

@Reasoning
PointsToConstraint represents a constraint in Andersen's analysis.

Constraint types:
1. ADDR_OF (p = &q): pts(p) ⊇ {q}
2. COPY (p = q): pts(p) ⊇ pts(q)
3. LOAD (p = *q): pts(p) ⊇ ⋃_{l ∈ pts(q)} pts(l)
4. STORE (*p = q): ∀l ∈ pts(p), pts(l) ⊇ pts(q)

Fields:
- constraint_type: Type constant (ADDR_OF, COPY, LOAD, STORE)
- lhs: Left-hand side pointer ID
- rhs: Right-hand side pointer/location ID
- instruction: Instruction that generated this constraint

Memory: Tier 3 (OWNED HEAP)
Size: 4 fields × 8 bytes = 32 bytes
@End Reasoning

Type called "PointsToConstraint":
    constraint_type as Integer  Note: Constraint type constant
    lhs as Integer              Note: Left-hand side ID
    rhs as Integer              Note: Right-hand side ID
    instruction as Integer      Note: Originating instruction pointer
End Type

Note: Field offsets: 0, 8, 16, 24

@Reasoning
PointsToGraph represents the complete points-to analysis results.

Contains:
- All abstract locations in the program
- Points-to sets for all pointer variables
- Constraints extracted from the program
- Worklist for iterative propagation

Used by alias analysis and escape analysis.

Fields:
- locations: List of AbstractLocation pointers
- pointer_to_set: Dictionary mapping pointer_id -> PointsToSet
- constraints: List of PointsToConstraint pointers
- next_location_id: Counter for generating unique location IDs
- worklist: Worklist for constraint propagation (pointer IDs to process)
- location_count: Number of abstract locations
- constraint_count: Number of constraints

Memory: Tier 3 (OWNED HEAP)
Size: 7 fields × 8 bytes = 56 bytes
@End Reasoning

Type called "PointsToGraph":
    locations as Integer            Note: List of AbstractLocation pointers
    pointer_to_set as Integer       Note: Dictionary pointer_id -> PointsToSet
    constraints as Integer          Note: List of PointsToConstraint pointers
    next_location_id as Integer     Note: Location ID counter
    worklist as Integer             Note: List of pointer IDs to process
    location_count as Integer       Note: Number of locations
    constraint_count as Integer     Note: Number of constraints
End Type

Note: Field offsets: 0, 8, 16, 24, 32, 40, 48

Note: ============================================================================
Note: POINTS-TO STRUCTURE INITIALIZATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Creates an AbstractLocation for an allocation site.

Memory: Tier 3 (OWNED HEAP) - 56 bytes
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_abstract_location" that takes location_id as Integer, allocation_site as Integer, type_info as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate AbstractLocation structure (56 bytes)
    Let location be proc allocate from Layout with 56
    If location equals 0:
        Display "create_abstract_location: allocation failed"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Set fields
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with location, 0, location_id
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with location, 8, allocation_site
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with location, 16, type_info
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with location, 24, 0 Note: is_heap = 0 (default stack)
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with location, 32, 0 Note: is_global = 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with location, 40, 0 Note: is_parameter = 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with location, 48, 0 Note: name = null

    Return location
End Process

@Reasoning
Creates a PointsToSet for a pointer variable.

Memory: Tier 3 (OWNED HEAP) - 32 bytes
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_points_to_set" that takes pointer_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate PointsToSet structure (32 bytes)
    Let pts be proc allocate from Layout with 32
    If pts equals 0:
        Display "create_points_to_set: allocation failed"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Set pointer_id
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with pts, 0, pointer_id

    Note: Create empty pointees set
    Let pointees be proc create from Set
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with pts, 8, pointees

    Note: Initialize flags
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with pts, 16, 0 Note: is_unknown = 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with pts, 24, 0 Note: is_null = 0

    Return pts
End Process

@Reasoning
Creates a constraint for Andersen's analysis.

Memory: Tier 3 (OWNED HEAP) - 32 bytes
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_constraint" that takes constraint_type as Integer, lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer, instruction as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate PointsToConstraint structure (32 bytes)
    Let constraint be proc allocate from Layout with 32
    If constraint equals 0:
        Display "create_constraint: allocation failed"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Set fields
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with constraint, 0, constraint_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with constraint, 8, lhs
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with constraint, 16, rhs
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with constraint, 24, instruction

    Return constraint
End Process

@Reasoning
Creates an empty PointsToGraph.

Memory: Tier 3 (OWNED HEAP) - 56 bytes
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_points_to_graph" returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate PointsToGraph structure (56 bytes)
    Let graph be proc allocate from Layout with 56
    If graph equals 0:
        Display "create_points_to_graph: allocation failed"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create empty collections
    Let locations be proc create from List
    Let pointer_to_set be proc create from Dictionary
    Let constraints be proc create from List
    Let worklist be proc create from List

    Note: Store in structure
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with graph, 0, locations
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with graph, 8, pointer_to_set
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with graph, 16, constraints
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with graph, 24, 0 Note: next_location_id = 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with graph, 32, worklist

    Note: Initialize counts
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with graph, 40, 0 Note: location_count = 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with graph, 48, 0 Note: constraint_count = 0

    Return graph
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ABSTRACT LOCATION MANAGEMENT
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Adds an abstract location to the points-to graph.

Returns: location_id of the added location
@End Reasoning

Process called "add_abstract_location" that takes graph as Integer, allocation_site as Integer, type_info as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph equals 0:
        Display "add_abstract_location: null graph"
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: Get next location ID
    Let next_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 24

    Note: Create location
    Let location be create_abstract_location(next_id, allocation_site, type_info)
    If location equals 0:
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: Add to locations list
    Let locations be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 0
    proc append from List with locations, location

    Note: Increment location ID counter
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with graph, 24, next_id plus 1

    Note: Increment location count
    Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 40
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with graph, 40, count plus 1

    Return next_id
End Process

@Reasoning
Gets or creates a points-to set for a pointer.

Returns: PointsToSet for the pointer
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_or_create_points_to_set" that takes graph as Integer, pointer_id as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph equals 0:
        Display "get_or_create_points_to_set: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get pointer_to_set dictionary
    Let pts_dict be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 8

    Note: Check if already exists
    Let pts be proc get from Dictionary with pts_dict, pointer_id
    If pts is not equal to 0:
        Return pts
    End If

    Note: Create new points-to set
    Set pts to create_points_to_set(pointer_id)
    If pts equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Store in dictionary
    proc set from Dictionary with pts_dict, pointer_id, pts

    Return pts
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTRAINT GENERATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Adds a constraint to the points-to graph.

Constraint types:
- ADDR_OF: p = &q (p points to location of q)
- COPY: p = q (p points to same as q)
- LOAD: p = *q (p points to what q's pointees point to)
- STORE: *p = q (q is stored through p)
@End Reasoning

Process called "add_constraint" that takes graph as Integer, constraint_type as Integer, lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer, instruction as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph equals 0:
        Display "add_constraint: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create constraint
    Let constraint be create_constraint(constraint_type, lhs, rhs, instruction)
    If constraint equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add to constraints list
    Let constraints be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 16
    proc append from List with constraints, constraint

    Note: Increment constraint count
    Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 48
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with graph, 48, count plus 1

    Note: Ensure points-to sets exist for lhs and rhs
    Let lhs_pts be get_or_create_points_to_set(graph, lhs)
    Let rhs_pts be get_or_create_points_to_set(graph, rhs)

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Extracts constraints from a MIR function.

Scans all instructions and generates appropriate constraints:
- Allocations generate abstract locations
- Pointer assignments generate COPY constraints
- Address-of operations generate ADDR_OF constraints
- Loads generate LOAD constraints
- Stores generate STORE constraints

Returns: 1 if successful
@End Reasoning

Process called "extract_constraints_from_mir" that takes graph as Integer, mir_function as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph equals 0 or mir_function equals 0:
        Display "extract_constraints_from_mir: null inputs"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get MIR CFG
    Let mir_cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with mir_function, 8
    If mir_cfg equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get blocks
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with mir_cfg, 16
    Let block_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with mir_cfg, 24

    Note: For each block
    Let b be 0
    While b is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc get from List with blocks, b

        Note: Get instructions
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with block, 16
        Let inst_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with block, 24

        Note: For each instruction
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than inst_count:
            Let inst be proc get from List with instructions, i

            Note: Get opcode (offset 0 in MIRNode)
            Let opcode be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst, 0

            Note: Get result value (destination pointer)
            Let result be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst, 8

            Note: Handle different instruction types
            Note: Allocation instructions (opcodes 20800-20899)
            If opcode is greater than or equal to 20800 and opcode is less than 20900:
                Note: Create abstract location for this allocation
                If result is not equal to 0:
                    Let value_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with result, 0
                    Let type_info be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with result, 8

                    Let location_id be add_abstract_location(graph, inst, type_info)

                    Note: Add ADDR_OF constraint: result points to this location
                    add_constraint(graph, 1, value_id, location_id, inst)  Note: ADDR_OF = 1
                End If
            End If

            Note: Copy/assignment instructions (opcodes 20000-20099)
            If opcode is greater than or equal to 20000 and opcode is less than 20100:
                If result is not equal to 0:
                    Let lhs_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with result, 0

                    Note: Get operands
                    Let operands be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst, 16
                    If operands is not equal to 0:
                        Let operand_count be proc length from List with operands
                        If operand_count is greater than 0:
                            Let rhs be proc get from List with operands, 0
                            If rhs is not equal to 0:
                                Let rhs_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with rhs, 0

                                Note: Add COPY constraint: lhs = rhs
                                add_constraint(graph, 2, lhs_id, rhs_id, inst)  Note: COPY = 2
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If

            Note: Load instructions (opcodes 20300-20349)
            If opcode is greater than or equal to 20300 and opcode is less than 20350:
                If result is not equal to 0:
                    Set lhs_id to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with result, 0

                    Note: Get pointer operand
                    Set operands to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst, 16
                    If operands is not equal to 0:
                        Set operand_count to proc length from List with operands
                        If operand_count is greater than 0:
                            Let ptr be proc get from List with operands, 0
                            If ptr is not equal to 0:
                                Let ptr_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ptr, 0

                                Note: Add LOAD constraint: lhs = *ptr
                                add_constraint(graph, 3, lhs_id, ptr_id, inst)  Note: LOAD = 3
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If

            Note: Store instructions (opcodes 20350-20399)
            If opcode is greater than or equal to 20350 and opcode is less than 20400:
                Note: Get operands
                Set operands to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst, 16
                If operands is not equal to 0:
                    Set operand_count to proc length from List with operands
                    If operand_count is greater than or equal to 2:
                        Set ptr to proc get from List with operands, 0
                        Let value be proc get from List with operands, 1

                        If ptr is not equal to 0 and value is not equal to 0:
                            Set ptr_id to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ptr, 0
                            Set value_id to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with value, 0

                            Note: Add STORE constraint: *ptr = value
                            add_constraint(graph, 4, ptr_id, value_id, inst)  Note: STORE = 4
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        Set b to b plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ANDERSEN'S POINTS-TO ANALYSIS (Inclusion-Based)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Adds a location to a points-to set and propagates changes.

If the pointee set actually changes, adds the pointer to the worklist
for constraint re-evaluation.

Returns: 1 if set changed, 0 if no change
@End Reasoning

Process called "add_pointee" that takes graph as Integer, pts as Integer, location_id as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph equals 0 or pts equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get pointees set
    Let pointees be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pts, 8

    Note: Check if already in set
    If proc contains from Set with pointees, location_id equals 1:
        Return 0  Note: No change
    End If

    Note: Add to set
    proc add from Set with pointees, location_id

    Note: Add pointer to worklist (changed, need to re-evaluate constraints)
    Let pointer_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pts, 0
    Let worklist be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 32
    proc append from List with worklist, pointer_id

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Computes points-to sets using Andersen's inclusion-based analysis.

Algorithm (worklist-based):
1. Initialize: Extract constraints from program
2. Process simple constraints (ADDR_OF)
3. Worklist iteration:
   - Pop pointer p from worklist
   - For each constraint involving p:
     - COPY (p = q): pts(p) ⊇ pts(q)
     - LOAD (p = *q): pts(p) ⊇ ⋃_{l ∈ pts(q)} pts(l)
     - STORE (*p = q): ∀l ∈ pts(p), pts(l) ⊇ pts(q)
   - If any pts set changes, add affected pointers to worklist
4. Repeat until worklist empty (fixed point)

Complexity: O(n³) worst case, but efficient in practice
Flow-insensitive: Same points-to set for all program points

Returns: 1 if successful
@End Reasoning

Process called "compute_points_to_andersen" that takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph equals 0:
        Display "compute_points_to_andersen: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get graph fields
    Let constraints be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 16
    Let constraint_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 48
    Let worklist be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 32
    Let pts_dict be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 8

    Note: Phase 1: Process ADDR_OF constraints (initialize points-to sets)
    Let c be 0
    While c is less than constraint_count:
        Let constraint be proc get from List with constraints, c
        Let type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with constraint, 0

        If type equals 1:  Note: ADDR_OF
            Let lhs be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with constraint, 8
            Let location_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with constraint, 16

            Note: pts(lhs) = {location_id}
            Let pts be get_or_create_points_to_set(graph, lhs)
            add_pointee(graph, pts, location_id)
        End If

        Set c to c plus 1
    End While

    Note: Phase 2: Iterative constraint solving (worklist algorithm)
    Let iteration be 0
    Let max_iterations be 1000

    While proc length from List with worklist is greater than 0 and iteration is less than max_iterations:
        Set iteration to iteration plus 1

        Note: Pop pointer from worklist
        Let pointer_id be proc get from List with worklist, 0
        proc remove_at from List with worklist, 0

        Note: Get points-to set for this pointer
        Let ptr_pts be proc get from Dictionary with pts_dict, pointer_id
        If ptr_pts equals 0:
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Process all constraints involving this pointer
        Set c to 0
        While c is less than constraint_count:
            Set constraint to proc get from List with constraints, c
            Set type to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with constraint, 0
            Set lhs to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with constraint, 8
            Let rhs be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with constraint, 16

            Note: COPY constraint: lhs = rhs
            If type equals 2:  Note: COPY
                Note: If rhs changed, propagate to lhs
                If rhs equals pointer_id:
                    Let lhs_pts be get_or_create_points_to_set(graph, lhs)
                    Let rhs_pointees be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ptr_pts, 8

                    Note: pts(lhs) ⊇ pts(rhs)
                    Let pointee_list be proc to_list from Set with rhs_pointees
                    Let pointee_count be proc length from List with pointee_list

                    Let p be 0
                    While p is less than pointee_count:
                        Set location_id to proc get from List with pointee_list, p
                        add_pointee(graph, lhs_pts, location_id)
                        Set p to p plus 1
                    End While
                End If
            End If

            Note: LOAD constraint: lhs = *rhs
            If type equals 3:  Note: LOAD
                Note: If rhs changed, propagate from rhs's pointees to lhs
                If rhs equals pointer_id:
                    Set lhs_pts to get_or_create_points_to_set(graph, lhs)
                    Set rhs_pointees to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ptr_pts, 8

                    Note: For each location l in pts(rhs)
                    Set pointee_list to proc to_list from Set with rhs_pointees
                    Set pointee_count to proc length from List with pointee_list

                    Set p to 0
                    While p is less than pointee_count:
                        Set location_id to proc get from List with pointee_list, p

                        Note: pts(lhs) ⊇ pts(location_id)
                        Let loc_pts be get_or_create_points_to_set(graph, location_id)
                        Let loc_pointees be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with loc_pts, 8

                        Let loc_pointee_list be proc to_list from Set with loc_pointees
                        Let loc_pointee_count be proc length from List with loc_pointee_list

                        Let q be 0
                        While q is less than loc_pointee_count:
                            Let target_id be proc get from List with loc_pointee_list, q
                            add_pointee(graph, lhs_pts, target_id)
                            Set q to q plus 1
                        End While

                        Set p to p plus 1
                    End While
                End If
            End If

            Note: STORE constraint: *lhs = rhs
            If type equals 4:  Note: STORE
                Note: If lhs changed, propagate rhs to lhs's pointees
                If lhs equals pointer_id:
                    Let rhs_pts be get_or_create_points_to_set(graph, rhs)
                    Let lhs_pointees be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ptr_pts, 8

                    Note: For each location l in pts(lhs)
                    Set pointee_list to proc to_list from Set with lhs_pointees
                    Set pointee_count to proc length from List with pointee_list

                    Set p to 0
                    While p is less than pointee_count:
                        Set location_id to proc get from List with pointee_list, p

                        Note: pts(location_id) ⊇ pts(rhs)
                        Set loc_pts to get_or_create_points_to_set(graph, location_id)
                        Set rhs_pointees to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with rhs_pts, 8

                        Let rhs_pointee_list be proc to_list from Set with rhs_pointees
                        Let rhs_pointee_count be proc length from List with rhs_pointee_list

                        Set q to 0
                        While q is less than rhs_pointee_count:
                            Set target_id to proc get from List with rhs_pointee_list, q
                            add_pointee(graph, loc_pts, target_id)
                            Set q to q plus 1
                        End While

                        Set p to p plus 1
                    End While
                End If
            End If

            Set c to c plus 1
        End While
    End While

    Note: Check for convergence
    If iteration equals max_iterations:
        Display "compute_points_to_andersen: max iterations reached (may not have converged)"
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: POINTS-TO QUERY INTERFACE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Queries the points-to set for a pointer.

Returns: PointsToSet for the pointer (or null if not found)
@End Reasoning

Process called "query_points_to" that takes graph as Integer, pointer_id as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph equals 0:
        Display "query_points_to: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get points-to set dictionary
    Let pts_dict be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 8

    Note: Look up points-to set
    Let pts be proc get from Dictionary with pts_dict, pointer_id

    Return pts
End Process

@Reasoning
Checks if two pointers may point to the same location (aliasing).

Returns:
- 1 if pointers may alias (pts(p) ∩ pts(q) ≠ ∅)
- 0 if pointers definitely don't alias (pts(p) ∩ pts(q) = ∅)
@End Reasoning

Process called "may_alias" that takes graph as Integer, ptr1_id as Integer, ptr2_id as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph equals 0:
        Return 1  Note: Conservative: assume may alias
    End If

    Note: Get points-to sets
    Let pts1 be query_points_to(graph, ptr1_id)
    Let pts2 be query_points_to(graph, ptr2_id)

    Note: If either is unknown or null, conservatively assume may alias
    If pts1 equals 0 or pts2 equals 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_unknown1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pts1, 16
    Let is_unknown2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pts2, 16

    If is_unknown1 equals 1 or is_unknown2 equals 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Check for intersection of pointee sets
    Let pointees1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pts1, 8
    Let pointees2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pts2, 8

    Let pointee_list1 be proc to_list from Set with pointees1
    Let count1 be proc length from List with pointee_list1

    Note: For each location in pts(ptr1)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count1:
        Let location_id be proc get from List with pointee_list1, i

        Note: Check if also in pts(ptr2)
        If proc contains from Set with pointees2, location_id equals 1:
            Return 1  Note: Found common location, may alias
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: No common locations found
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Gets the abstract location for a pointer's allocation site.

Useful for determining where a pointer was allocated.

Returns: AbstractLocation pointer (or 0 if not found)
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_allocation_location" that takes graph as Integer, pointer_id as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get points-to set
    Let pts be query_points_to(graph, pointer_id)
    If pts equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get pointees
    Let pointees be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pts, 8
    Let pointee_list be proc to_list from Set with pointees
    Let count be proc length from List with pointee_list

    Note: If points to exactly one location, return it
    If count equals 1:
        Let location_id be proc get from List with pointee_list, 0

        Note: Find location in locations list
        Let locations be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 0
        Let location_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 40

        Let i be 0
        While i is less than location_count:
            Let location be proc get from List with locations, i
            Let loc_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with location, 0

            If loc_id equals location_id:
                Return location
            End If

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Points to multiple or zero locations
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VERIFICATION AND DEBUGGING
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Verifies points-to graph correctness.

Checks:
1. All constraints reference valid pointers
2. No cycles in constraint graph (optional, expensive)
3. Points-to sets are consistent

Returns: 1 if valid, 0 if errors found
@End Reasoning

Process called "verify_points_to_graph" that takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph equals 0:
        Display "verify_points_to_graph: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let errors be 0

    Note: Verify constraint count
    Let constraints be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 16
    Let constraint_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 48
    Let actual_count be proc length from List with constraints

    If actual_count is not equal to constraint_count:
        Display "verify_points_to_graph: constraint count mismatch"
        Set errors to errors plus 1
    End If

    Note: Verify location count
    Let locations be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 0
    Let location_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 40
    Let actual_loc_count be proc length from List with locations

    If actual_loc_count is not equal to location_count:
        Display "verify_points_to_graph: location count mismatch"
        Set errors to errors plus 1
    End If

    Note: Verify all constraints have valid types
    Let c be 0
    While c is less than constraint_count:
        Let constraint be proc get from List with constraints, c
        Let type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with constraint, 0

        If type is less than 1 or type is greater than 4:
            Display "verify_points_to_graph: invalid constraint type"
            Set errors to errors plus 1
        End If

        Set c to c plus 1
    End While

    If errors equals 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Prints points-to graph for debugging.

Displays:
- Number of locations and constraints
- For each pointer: points-to set
- For each constraint: type and operands
@End Reasoning

Process called "print_points_to_graph" that takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph equals 0:
        Display "print_points_to_graph: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Display "=== Points-To Analysis Results ==="

    Note: Print summary
    Let location_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 40
    Let constraint_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 48

    Display "Abstract Locations: "
    Display location_count
    Display ", Constraints: "
    Display constraint_count

    Note: Print abstract locations
    Display ""
    Display "Abstract Locations:"
    Let locations be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 0

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than location_count:
        Let location be proc get from List with locations, i
        Let loc_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with location, 0
        Let alloc_site be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with location, 8
        Let is_heap be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with location, 24
        Let is_global be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with location, 32

        Display "  Location "
        Display loc_id
        Display ": alloc="
        Display alloc_site
        Display ", heap="
        Display is_heap
        Display ", global="
        Display is_global

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Print points-to sets
    Display ""
    Display "Points-To Sets:"
    Let pts_dict be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 8
    Let pointer_ids be proc keys from Dictionary with pts_dict
    Let ptr_count be proc length from List with pointer_ids

    Set i to 0
    While i is less than ptr_count:
        Let pointer_id be proc get from List with pointer_ids, i
        Let pts be proc get from Dictionary with pts_dict, pointer_id

        Display "  Pointer "
        Display pointer_id
        Display " -> {"

        Let pointees be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with pts, 8
        Let pointee_list be proc to_list from Set with pointees
        Let pointee_count be proc length from List with pointee_list

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than pointee_count:
            Set loc_id to proc get from List with pointee_list, j
            Display loc_id
            If j is less than (pointee_count minus 1):
                Display ", "
            End If
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Display "}"

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Print constraints
    Display ""
    Display "Constraints:"
    Let constraints be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with graph, 16

    Let c be 0
    While c is less than constraint_count:
        Let constraint be proc get from List with constraints, c
        Let type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with constraint, 0
        Let lhs be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with constraint, 8
        Let rhs be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with constraint, 16

        Display "  "
        Display lhs

        If type equals 1:
            Display " = &"
        Otherwise If type equals 2:
            Display " = "
        Otherwise If type equals 3:
            Display " = *"
        Otherwise If type equals 4:
            Display "* = "
        End If

        Display rhs

        Set c to c plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process
